columns.text:
The **spot rate** is the *exchange rate in a spot trade*. The **spot trade** is an agreement to exchange currencies based on the exchange rate on that date and must be settled within two business days.
&nbsp;

A **forward trade** is an agreement to *exchange currency in the future*. The *exchange rate in the agreement* of a forward trade is called a **forward exchange rate.**

First, we will determine the value of investment in dollars.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Investment in \$} &= \dfrac{\text{Investment in € }}{\text{Spot Rate}}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{€ 10,500,000}}{\text{€ 0.94}}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 11,170,213}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The investment is worth **$ 11,170,213**.

Next, we will determine the expected cash flow in dollar in year 1.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Cash Flow in \$} &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in € }}{\text{Exchange Rate}}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{€ 1,700,000}}{\text{€ 0.9353}}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 1,817,599}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The cash flow in Year 1 when converted into dollars is **$ 1,817,599**.

Next, we will determine the expected cash flow in dollar in year 2.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Cash Flow in \$} &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in € }}{\text{Exchange Rate}}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{€ 2,400,000}}{\text{€ 0.9306 }}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 2,578,981}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The cash flow in Year 2 when converted into dollars is **$ 2,578,981**.

Lastly, we will determine the expected cash flow in dollar in year 3. However, we will consider the selling price of the project at the end of three years worth € 7,900,000.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Cash Flow in \$} &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in € +Investment after 3 Years }}{\text{Exchange Rate}}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{€ 3,300,000 + € 7,900,000}}{\text{€ 0.9260 }}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{€ 11,200,000}}{\text{€ 0.9260 }}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 12,095,032}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The cash flow in Year 3 when converted into dollars is **$ 12,095,032**.

First, we will get the present value of Year 1:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value } &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in \$ }}{\text{(1 + Discount Rate)}^t}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 1,817,599 }}{\text{1 +.13 }^1}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 1,817,599 }}{\text{1.13 }^1}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 1,817,599 }}{\text{1.13 }}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 1,608,495}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The present value in Year 1 is **$ 1,608,495**.

Next, we will get the present value of Year 2:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value } &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in \$ }}{\text{(1 + Discount Rate)}^t}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 2,578,981 }}{\text{1 +.13 }^2}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 2,578,981 }}{\text{1.13 }^2}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 2,578,981 }}{\text{1.2769 }}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 2,019,720}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The present value in Year 2 is **$ 2,019,720**.

Lastly, we will get the present value of Year 3:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value } &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in \$ }}{\text{(1 + Discount Rate)}^t}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 12,095,032 }}{\text{1 +.13 }^3}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 12,095,032 }}{\text{1.13 }^3}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 12,095,032}}{\text{1.4429 }}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 8,382,446}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The present value in Year 2 is **$ 8,382,446**.
